details.title: Best-known autocorrelation peak sidelobe levels for binary codes of length 71 to 105
details.abstract: Best-known binary code autocorrelation peak sidelobe levels (PSLs) are updated for lengths 71 to 105. For lengths 71 to 82, codes with PSL 4 are found, establishing 4 as almost certainly the optimal value for these lengths. PSL-5 codes are produced for all lengths from 83 to 105, in many cases improving on best-known values.
details.journal_title: IEEE Transactions on Aerospace and Electronic Systems
